### ============================================
### REGISTRATION HISTORY TESTS (Phase 4)
### ============================================
### Testing soft delete and registration history
### ============================================

@baseUrl = http://localhost:5000/api
@studentEmail = gm7605@myamu.ac.in
@studentPassword = azx

### ============================================
### 1. LOGIN AS STUDENT
### ============================================
POST http://localhost:5000/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "{{studentEmail}}",
  "password": "{{studentPassword}}"
}

### Save the token from response and use it below
@token = YOUR_TOKEN_HERE

### ============================================
### 2. GET AVAILABLE COURSES
### ============================================
GET {{baseUrl}}/courses/available
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### ============================================
### 3. REGISTER FOR A COURSE
### ============================================
POST {{baseUrl}}/courses/register
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "course_code": "ELBEA301"
}

### ============================================
### 4. GET DASHBOARD (Check registered courses)
### ============================================
GET {{baseUrl}}/student/dashboard
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Should show registeredCourses array with the course

### ============================================
### 5. DROP THE COURSE (Soft Delete)
### ============================================
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/courses/drop/ELBEA301
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Should set deleted_at timestamp, not hard delete

### ============================================
### 6. GET DASHBOARD AGAIN (Course should be gone)
### ============================================
GET {{baseUrl}}/student/dashboard
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### registeredCourses should be empty now

### ============================================
### 7. GET REGISTRATION HISTORY (Should show dropped course)
### ============================================
GET {{baseUrl}}/student/registration-history
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Should show:
### - history array with the dropped course
### - status: "Dropped"
### - droppedAt: timestamp
### - statistics with droppedRegistrations count

### ============================================
### 8. TRY TO DROP SAME COURSE AGAIN (Should Fail)
### ============================================
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/courses/drop/ELBEA301
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Should return 404: "Not registered for this course"
### Because deleted_at is not null

### ============================================
### 9. RE-REGISTER FOR THE SAME COURSE
### ============================================
POST {{baseUrl}}/courses/register
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "course_code": "ELBEA301"
}

### Should work - creates new registration record

### ============================================
### 10. GET REGISTRATION HISTORY AGAIN
### ============================================
GET {{baseUrl}}/student/registration-history
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Should show:
### - 2 records for ELBEA301
### - One with status "Dropped" (old)
### - One with status "Active" (new)

### ============================================
### TESTING CHECKLIST
### ============================================
### ✅ Test 1: Student login works
### ✅ Test 2: Can view available courses
### ✅ Test 3: Can register for a course
### ✅ Test 4: Dashboard shows registered course
### ✅ Test 5: Drop course sets deleted_at (soft delete)
### ✅ Test 6: Dashboard no longer shows dropped course
### ✅ Test 7: Registration history shows dropped course
### ✅ Test 8: Cannot drop already dropped course
### ✅ Test 9: Can re-register for dropped course
### ✅ Test 10: History shows both records

### ============================================
### EXPECTED BEHAVIOR
### ============================================
### 1. Dropping a course sets deleted_at timestamp
### 2. Dashboard filters out soft-deleted registrations
### 3. Available courses filters out soft-deleted registrations
### 4. Registration history shows ALL registrations
### 5. Can re-register for previously dropped courses
### 6. Each registration has unique registration_id
